data.enText: not genuine; appearing to be sth it is not
made to look like sth else

data.chText: 别顶着太阳出去了，擦点棕褐色油装作太阳晒的就行了。
data.enText: Don't go out in the sun─get a fake tan from a bottle.
an object such as a work of art, a coin or a piece of jewellery that is not genuine but has been made to look as if it is

data.chText: 所有这些画结果证实都是赝品。
data.enText: All the paintings proved to be fakes.
a person who pretends to be what they are not in order to cheat people
to make sth false appear to be genuine, especially in order to cheat sb

data.chText: 她伪造了她母亲在文件上的签字。
data.enText: She faked her mother's signature on the document.

data.chText: 他策划了这次事故以便造成他自己死亡的假象。
data.enText: He arranged the accident in order to fake his own death.

data.chText: 假装，佯装，装出（某种感情、有病等）
data.enText: to pretend to have a particular feeling, illness, etc.

data.chText: 她并不是真的病了，不过是假装的。
data.enText: She's not really sick─she's just faking it .

data.text: artificial ♦ synthetic ♦ false ♦ man-made ♦ fake ♦ imitation

data.chText: 以上各词均指假的、非天然的、人造的。
data.enText: These words all describe things that are not real, or not naturally produced or grown.
made or produced to copy sth natural; not real
made by combining chemical substances rather than being produced naturally by plants or animals

data.chText: 指非天然的、非天生的、假的：

data.enText: made to look like sth else; not real

data.chText: 一件人造毛皮的短上衣

data.enText: [only before noun] made to look like sth else; not real
She would never wear imitation pearls.

means: 假装，佯装，装出(某种感情、有病等)

tr: (football) a deceptive move made by a football player
not what it seems to be
a person who makes deceitful pretenses
speak insincerely or without regard for facts or truths
example: The politician was not well prepared for the debate and faked it

tr: make a copy of with the intent to deceive
tamper, with the purpose of deception
being an imitation of the genuine article
example: a purse of simulated alligator hide

value.def: A fake fur or a fake painting, for example, is a fur or painting that has been made to look valuable or genuine, usually in order to deceive people.

example.ex: The bank manager is said to have issued fake certificates.
example.tran: 据说那个银行经理曾出具伪造的凭证。

posc.def: A fake is something that is fake.

example.ex: It is filled with famous works of art, and every one of them is a fake.
example.tran: 这里满是艺术名品，但每一件都是赝品。

value.def: If someone fakes something, they try to make it look valuable or genuine, although in fact it is not.

example.ex: It's safer to fake a tan with make-up rather than subject your complexion to the harsh rays of the sun...
example.tran: 用化妆品打造出古铜色的皮肤比让皮肤受太阳的暴晒更为安全。

example.ex: He faked his own death last year to collect on a $1 million insurance policy.
example.tran: 去年，他诈死以骗取100万美元的保险金。

value.def: Someone who is a fake is not what they claim to be, for example because they do not have the qualifications that they claim to have.
If you fake a feeling, emotion, or reaction, you pretend that you are experiencing it when you are not.

example.tran: 乔恩装作若无其事的样子。

example.ex: Maturity and emotional sophistication can't be faked.
example.tran: 成熟和情感上的老道是装不出来的。

trans: 人造毛皮；人造皮毛；人造毛
隐藏的真相；头部假动作
